message.content: From the diagram, we have the equation \[100(2a) + 10(2b) + 2(c+d) = 100(1) + 10(0) + (1+0).\]Multiplying out and simplifying both sides gives \[200a + 20b + 2c + 2d = 101.\]Dividing by 2 gives \[100a + 10b + c + d = 50 + \tfrac{1}{2}.\]The left side of this equation is an integer, so the right side must be an integer.  Since $50$ is an integer, it follows that $\tfrac{1}{2}$ must represent $0.$  Therefore, \[100a + 10b + c + d = 50,\]which means \[a + b + c + d = \boxed{5}.\]
